  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Thus, GNNs can complement or even replace handcrafted feature representations widely used in the natural sciences.",
    "Since 2018, various GNN models have been proposed to improve prediction performance, such as CGCNN 22, SchNet 20, MEGNet 23, iCGCNN 24, ALIGNN 25, and coGN 26, among others.",
    "These architectures all use structure graph representation as input, also incorporating slightly different additional information, convolution operators, and neural network architectures 20, 23, 24.",
    "Despite this progress, there are still major problems with the application of GNNs in the fields of chemistry and materials: First, nested graph networks like ALIGNN and coNGN 26 have substantially more trainable parameters, leading to higher training costs compared to nonnested graph networks.",
    "These nested graph networks maintain their advantages only on some crystal datasets."
  ],
